maml:description.maml:para: The New-AzureIPTag cmdlet creates an Azure IPTag object. You can use a IPTag object when you want to reserve an IPAddress with IPTags. For any particular IPTag, you should create a corresponding IPTag object and then provide a list of these IPTag objects to New-AzureReservedIP as a parameter.
IPTagType of the IPTag. Its value can be IPAddressClassification, AvailabilityZone or FirstPartyUsage.
Value of the IPTagType. Its value would depend upon the IPTagType.
IPTagType of the IPTag. Its value can be IPAddressClassification, AvailabilityZone or FirstPartyUsage.
Value of the IPTagType. Its value would depend upon the IPTagType.

dev:remarks.maml:para: This example creates an IPTag with IPTagType "FirstPartyUsage" and its value as "InfrastructureTenants", if the customer is allowed to reserve an IP Address with this Tag, specifying this $Iptag as a parameter to New-AzureReservedIP should reserve it.
